  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The ENR record as currently constituted has a field holding the fork id of the node.  This fork ID should change when we roll over to the new fork.\r\n\r\nWe should broadcast the forkID of of the best _known_ block and when that crosses the barrier accept that fork id.  We will also need to write the forkid to the persistent storage when needed.\r\n\r\nSo probably a listener on the blockchain object, that has a reference to the protocol schedule and whatever class holds the ENR.  When we detect a change in the listener from observed values we fire off an event to the object calculating the ENR to rebuild it.",
